des:
You can simply ask Alexa to turn a lamp on, off or dim, just talk to Alexa through your speaker.

To connect your devices to Alexa, follow a few simple steps:
(one). Download the "" AGL HOME "" present in both app stores;
(two). Create your account in the application;
(3). Have your smart product installed or close at hand;
(4). Set the product in the AGL HOME APP and choose an appropriate name, as the device will be used by the AGL HOME skill;
(5). Download the Alexa app from any app store;
(6). Configure your speaker in the app;
(7). Find the skill "" AGL HOME "" in the list of Alexa skills;
(8). Enable AGL HOME skill, then you will be taken to AGL HOME login page;
(9). Enter your AGL HOME username and password;
(10). All steps are finished.

Take the opportunity to voice control your IoT products with phrases with the following:
"Alexa, turn on the kitchen light" "
"Alexa, turn off the kitchen light" "
"Alexa, make the light in the room less bright" "
"Alexa, make the room brighter" "
"Alexa, set the room light brightness to 20 percent" "
